etsysDiagnosticMessageMIB.name: etsysDiagnosticMessageMIB

revisions.description: Added a textual convention to provide a display hint for the etsysDiagnosticMessageDetailsText object.
Added Enterasys copyright notice and corrected some text.
Removed the import of BITS from SNMPv2-SMI.
The initial version of this MIB module.

etsysDiagnosticMessageMIB.contactinfo: Postal: Enterasys Networks 50 Minuteman Rd. Andover, MA 01810-1008 USA Phone: +1 978 684 1000 E-mail: support@enterasys.com WWW: http://www.enterasys.com
etsysDiagnosticMessageMIB.description: This MIB module defines a portion of the SNMP enterprise MIBs under the Enterasys enterprise OID pertaining to the retrieval of diagnostic messages.

LongAdminString.name: LongAdminString
LongAdminString.description: A size extended version of an SnmpAdminString as defined in RFC2571.
LongAdminString.reference: RFC2571 (An Architecture for Describing SNMP Management Frameworks)

etsysDiagnosticMessageCount.name: etsysDiagnosticMessageCount
etsysDiagnosticMessageCount.description: The number of messages logged on this entity since the beginning of time. This value must be persistent. There should be no facility to clear this value.

etsysDiagnosticMessageChanges.name: etsysDiagnosticMessageChanges
etsysDiagnosticMessageChanges.description: The number of changes to the message log since the last reboot. Changes should include, clearing the message log, deleting a message, and the logging of new messages.

etsysDiagnosticMessageTable.name: etsysDiagnosticMessageTable
etsysDiagnosticMessageTable.description: This table lists a summary of the diagnostic messages stored on the managed entity.

etsysDiagnosticMessageEntry.name: etsysDiagnosticMessageEntry
etsysDiagnosticMessageEntry.description: An entry describing a particular diagnostic message. Every message that is stored in non-volatile memory is required to appear in this table.

etsysDiagnosticMessageIndex.name: etsysDiagnosticMessageIndex
etsysDiagnosticMessageIndex.description: A unique arbitrary identifier for this message. For stateless message log implementations it may be valid only while etsysDiagnosticMessageChanges remains unchanged.

etsysDiagnosticMessageTime.name: etsysDiagnosticMessageTime
etsysDiagnosticMessageTime.description: The time and date that this message was stored.

etsysDiagnosticMessageType.name: etsysDiagnosticMessageType
etsysDiagnosticMessageType.description: A description of the type of message shown in this entry.

etsysDiagnosticMessageSummary.name: etsysDiagnosticMessageSummary
etsysDiagnosticMessageSummary.description: A brief summary of the diagnostic message.

etsysDiagnosticMessageFWRevision.name: etsysDiagnosticMessageFWRevision
etsysDiagnosticMessageFWRevision.description: The string representing the version of firmware running on the the managed entity at the time the message was stored.

etsysDiagnosticMessageStatus.name: etsysDiagnosticMessageStatus
etsysDiagnosticMessageStatus.description: A list of attributes associated with this message. Generally these attributes would be considered exceptional, but could potentially be extended to indicate any number of conditions.

etsysDiagnosticMessageDetailsTable.name: etsysDiagnosticMessageDetailsTable
etsysDiagnosticMessageDetailsTable.description: This table contains the complete diagnostic messages for entries in the etsysDiagnosticMessageSummaryTable. This allows a message of virtually unlimited length to be accessible via SNMP.

etsysDiagnosticMessageDetailsEntry.name: etsysDiagnosticMessageDetailsEntry
etsysDiagnosticMessageDetailsEntry.description: An entry describing a particular fragment of a message.

etsysDiagnosticMessageDetailsIndex.name: etsysDiagnosticMessageDetailsIndex
etsysDiagnosticMessageDetailsIndex.description: A unique arbitrary identifier for this message fragment. Ideally this index should have the values 1 - n, where 'n' is the number of message fragments. It, at a minimum, must be chosen such that the lexicographical ordering will allow the fragments to be assembled in the proper order.

etsysDiagnosticMessageDetailsText.name: etsysDiagnosticMessageDetailsText
etsysDiagnosticMessageDetailsText.description: The text that makes up a fragment of a message.

etsysDiagnosticMessageDetailsStatus.name: etsysDiagnosticMessageDetailsStatus
etsysDiagnosticMessageDetailsStatus.description: A list of attributes associated with this message segment.

etsysDiagnosticMessageCompliance.name: etsysDiagnosticMessageCompliance
etsysDiagnosticMessageCompliance.description: The compliance statement for managed entities that support diagnostic message logs.
